      • processRecords

        public java.util.List processRecords(org.json.simple.JSONObject object,
                                     java.lang.String type_id,
                                     java.lang.String setRecordsType)
        Checks if an object exists. If exists, sets operation type to UPDATE otherwise to ADD. Checks if elements of object exists. If an element exists, replace element and element set values with the appropriate values received from Omeka. if an element does not exist, throw an error for that particular element.
        Parameters:
        object - object information
        type_id -
        setRecordsType -
        Returns:
        Type of the operation to be performed (ADD or UPDATE) and modified object

      • addLocation

        public void addLocation(java.lang.String item)
        Adds location to a record. Currently only one location can be added in omeka. Before adding a new location, existing location is removed. Location will be added if 'locations' variable is not empty. In case it is empty existing location will be removed, leaving no location in omeka for this record.
        Parameters:
        item -
